evidence for rites of death and burial in the Maya lowlands, from which he creates models of royal Maya funerary behavior. Exploring ancient Maya attitudes toward death expressed at well-known sites such as Tikal, Guatemala, and Copan, Honduras, as well as less-explored archaeological locations, Fitzsimmons reconstructs royal mortuary rites and expands our understanding of key Maya concepts including the afterlife and ancestor veneration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aHuman remains (Archaeology)zMexico. 0aMayan languagesxWriting. 0aMayasxFuneral customs and rites. 0aMayasxKings and rulersxDeath and burial. 0aTombszMexico. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Archaeology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/71890640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292793705423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292793705/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK